node.text: Wanted to share a short clip of song I wrote recently with two of my best friends @alyssabonagura and @shanestevensmusic ❤️ I’m not going to divulge too much on it but leave it up to your interpretation ❤️ I know I sound like the girl who “sang” wolf but I am putting new music out soon with @warnermusicnashville and it’s going to be magic✨

node.text: Around this time in 2019 I headed into the studio to cover the biggest song of the year. I played it on tour and had the time of my life! So excited to go back on the road and see y’all. We are in the middle of putting together a spring 2022 tour and I am SO pumped!!!! Comment and let me know where you wanna see me play!!

node.text:
I work out 3 to 4 times a week and they pretty much look like this with certain variations whether were doing more upper body or lower body. Btw my trainer @klugfitness is the bomb.com! Transforming me!

-I usually don’t eat first thing in the morning but if I do I will have a bowl of oatmeal or toast. I  have coffee with cream (can’t give that up) after my work out I have a protein shake (20grams) 
-For lunch lunch I will have 4 to 6 ounces chicken salad or chicken over rice. 
-For snack if I’m really not watching I will have chips and salsa but if I’m really watching myself I will have a homemade protein energy ball (those are in my @justfeedme cook book) around 3 o’clock I have an espresso 

-For dinner I will either have a lean red meat like flank steak with vegetables ,  chili from my book or the same kind of thing chicken and rice vegetables or my fit-enchiladas from my first book ! -For dessert I will have a piece of chocolate. 

-Now you guys know I love to eat so this is only when I’m really watching myself and wanting to tone up even more and lean up a little bit more. 

🤩You guys message me asking me all the time what I eat in a day and what I do so I figured I would share. It’s pretty vague but if you have any detailed questions feel free to comment below and I will try to answer!

node.title: My work out 💪 and what I eat in a day

node.text:
Colorado will always hold a special place in our hearts. We will always consider it our first home.  It’s the place @ericdecker was drafted and played 4 years for the Denver Broncos, it’s the place we fell in love , got married, and had all three of our babies. One of the hardest places to leave. So it would only make sense to wanna open a @KITTENISH location in the Denver area so we can come back even more.  We have narrowed it down to two locations but are having the hardest time deciding what the perfect spot would be. We really really need your help !! 
Please comment below and let us know the most ideal location to shop. (in honor of opening a KITTENISH store in Denver I decided to post a throwback of Eric‘s highlights as a Denver bronco)  We are so excited!!!!!!!! Let’s us know 👇

node.text: A quick little highlight reel of our work out today! We did a few more things in between but here’s the gist of our morning sessions! After we work out (usually an hour with warm ups included) I have 25 grams of protein and then 2 hours after that will have lunch. Usually chicken and veggies and then a healthy snack and then dinner I make whatever I want to eat with the fam but i try to keep it clean ingredients! If y’all like this stuff I will post more here and there❤️ @ericdecker @klugfitness

node.text: This is this song I wrote recently with my good friend @bccoconutman and the talented Rob Persaud. Would love to know if y’all think this one should make the album? I’m so excited to keep sharing clips and little teases of all the music I’ve been working on. I am so proud of the music I’ve been making!! I have evolved as a woman and so has my music. I love that I’m able to take y’all on this journey with me. This record will be The most special album I’ve ever made ✨✨✨

Enjoy this recipe and let me know if you’d like me to make more videos like this and what recipe I should do next! Link in bio to purchase my cookbook if you haven’t gotten your hands on it yet✨ @justfeedme

node.text: When I was a basketball cheerleader in 10th grade we learned this step for the bleachers. Fast forward I was in the studio and started to do the step because I thought it would make a cool sound in a song. That song became “Blue Jeans.” It came out in 2009 on my first debut album self titled. It was my masterpiece. I begged my label to release it, but it was SO different being country and pop with so many other influences at that time, they were afraid… so they released a song called “Wanted” instead🥰. Still one of my favorite songs to write and create. Would love to see y’all learn this routine too and and tag me!  Follow me on TikTok for more shenanigans … posting a new one today!! Link in bio

You know this past year has been crazy, I’ve had so many changes to my routine and noticed my skin could use some extra TLC. The 3-in-1 treatments are all non-invasive and require ZERO downtime, so you get glowing skin immediately ✨ not to mention the improvement in my skin texture and brightness.

With four customizable treatments available - Hydrate, Revive, Balance, and Illuminate (my personal fave) - @geneo_us has a skin solution for every age, skin type, and season! 🙌

node.text: I was told I would feel some sort of travel blues once I got back home.  I also predicted I would as well.  But as soon as we came back I was so happy to be home and be in our beds and see our dogs and get the kids back on some sort of schedule. that I didn’t experience that at all.  But it’s been now three weeks and today It kind of set in just a little.  We truly had an experience of a lifetime that I will never forget. It wasn’t always easy at times traveling from city to city on multiple planes and trains and automobiles with three little ones but it was such an adventure and I miss it today. I’m really glad we were able to give our kids such an experience that they will cherish forever❤️❤️❤️ I know traveling with children can be hard but I do recommend it when you can. It really brings your family so close even if you are already close.  One of my favorite memories was ordering room service with the kids and watching the greatest showman all in bed with our food trays all snuggled up as a family it was so special❤️❤️ where to next? ✈️ 📸 @santorinidress
